<TITLE> Govt suspends FBCCI elections </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 10 (bdnews24.com) - The commerce ministry Tuesday postponed the upcoming election for the Federation of Bangladesh Chambers of Commerce and Industry, the apex business body said in a statement. The FBCCI election for 2007-09 had been scheduled for Aug 16. "The upcoming election of the FBCCI has been postponed until further order," senior assistant secretary of the commerce ministry, Ashraful Islam Khan, said. An emergency meeting of the FBCCI Election Board presided over by its chairman Ali Ashraf decided to urgently convey the government's order to the members. Helal Uddin, an FBCCI director, told bdnews24.com that a section of reformist businessmen would hold a press conference Wednesday to demand direct elections to all posts in the FBCCI. bdnew
